{"title":"The Falling","author":{"name":"Jane Hirshfield"},"publishDate":"2011-10-24","lines":[{"line":"You turn towards meteor showers in August,","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"wishing yourself like that:","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"bright and burning wholly out.","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"When feeling finally comes it is","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"that falling, matter breaking away","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"from air, the sound","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"of crickets moving through the grass like fire—","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"and the strangely twisted metal","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"in the field that a child finds:","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"residue, crown.","stanza":1,"number":10},{"line":"Then there’s the story of the Chinese sage,","stanza":1,"number":11},{"line":"in anger and despair, who cut his body away in pieces,","stanza":1,"number":12},{"line":"flung them into the lake.","stanza":1,"number":13},{"line":"Each one, becoming finned and whole, swims off.","stanza":1,"number":14}]}